titleproper.value:
Guide to the Records of the RISM Cross-Cultural 
                    <lb/> Comparisons of Aging and Longevity Study 
                    <lb/>
                    <num>RISM RG 15</num>

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2016-03-16T09:56-0400</date>

unittitle.value:
Records of the RISM Cross-Cultural Comparisons of
                <lb/> Aging and Longevity Study (The Longevity Study)
                <lb/>

p.value:
Additionally, please note that this collection is stored 
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.nyu.edu/library/bobst/research/arch/longevity.htm">
                    <archref> offsite </archref> </extref>, and you must contact the repository to schedule access.

Based on Dr. Benet's research in Russia, Dr. Vera Rubin, director of RISM, proposed that Dr. Benet undertake a major study of the long-living people who had been her chief Abkhasian subjects. Dr. Benet's study led to the development of a US-USSR multidisciplinary research project on longevity, which involved both Soviet and American social scientists. The study was known as the Cross-Cultural Comparisons of Aging and Longevity Study.
